-- AngloGold, Billiton, Reunert, Sasol May Be Active in Johannesburg Trading
-- Ron Derby
-- 2010-07-06T05:55:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/bhp-billiton-and-sasol-may-be-active-south-africa-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  
 South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  fell 131.89,
or 0.5 percent, to 26,182.67.  
 AngloGold Ashanti Ltd.  (ANG SJ): Gold weakened for a second
day as the dollar climbed, cutting the metal’s appeal as a store
of value. AngloGold, Africa’s largest gold producer, dropped
4.75 rand, or 1.5 percent, to 314.25 rand.  
 BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BIL SJ): The world’s largest mining
company was raised to “buy” from “hold” at Independent
Research GmbH. The company fell 5.15 rand, or 2.6 percent, to
196.55 rand.  
 Separately, copper advanced for a third day as demand for
the industrial metal reduced inventories to a seven-month low.  
 Reunert Ltd.  (RLO SJ): The engineering and electronics
company said it will pay a preference dividend on Aug. 2 of 5.5
cents per share for the half year through June 30. Reunert added
1 cent, or less than 0.1 percent, to 57 rand.  
 Sasol Ltd.  (SOL SJ): Crude oil dropped for a sixth day in
New York on concern that the pace of economic recovery is
slowing in Europe and China, stalling a rebound in fuel demand.
Sasol, the world’s biggest maker of motor fuel from coal, fell
55 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 276.20 rand.  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows on July 2. U.S.
markets were closed for a public holiday yesterday:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) rose 0.2 percent to $17.34.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) increased 0.6 percent to $40.75.
BHP Billiton Plc (BBL US) gained 1.1 percent to $52.15. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) rallied 0.7 percent to $4.29. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) advanced 0.3 percent to $12.83. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) added 1.2 percent to $10.31. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) climbed 1.8 percent to $23.51. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
increased 1.1 percent to $3.80. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose 1
percent to $35.76.  
